The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Thursday, May 06, 2004  Ooty races postponed 
 BY OUR TURF CORRESPONDENT				 										Calcutta: The stewards, Madras Race Club (MRC) have decided to postpone Thursdays Udhagamandalam races by a day. The inter-state betting on Ooty races, therefore, will be conducted by the Royal Calcutta Turf Club (RCTC) on Friday, according to an RCTC notification. 				 										The Udhagamandalam races scheuled for Wednesday, Thursday and Friday have been postponed due to rains, according to PTI from Chennai. The stewards, MRC have, therefore, rescheduled Wednesdays races on Friday while Thursdays programme will be conducted on Saturday. Races scheduled for Friday would now be held on Sunday, the MRC said in a press release.
